        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 21 at 2:25PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 225 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Neely Henry Lake, or near Rainbow City, moving south at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Rainbow City, Ashville, Ragland, Steele, Neely Henry Lake, and Neely
Henry Dam.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
